  "prompt": "How often do you buy new smart phones?",
  "response": "The frequency of buying new smartphones varies widely among individuals based on personal preferences, needs, and budget. Some people upgrade every year to keep up with the latest technology, while others may wait two to three years or longer, choosing to stick with a device until it no longer meets their needs or performance standards. Factors influencing the decision to buy a new smartphone include advancements in technology, changes in features, battery life, and personal circumstances. How often do you tend to upgrade your smartphone?",
